value.0: Welcome, how may I help you?
Very well - are you here to deliver some supplies then?
Sorry, no. Someone has already delivered supplies to us recently. Perhaps try another nearby fortress?
Ah, yes. We certainly coulld use some additional supplies!
Sorry, no, someone has already collected my excess goods.
Ah, yes, I have some things that can be traded...
Sorry, no, someone has already collected my goods.
Ah, yes, I have some items for the good of the barony.
What trade goods would you like to deliver at this time?
Thank you. Here is your coin. Do you have any other goods you wish to deliver?
I'm glad you asked! Most of these adventuring sorts just foolishly purchase some goods and set out on the road. Then they die to the bandits or wolves...But you're not like them, eh?

So, it's fairly simple. There are five Baronies in Brost County, if you count the Mayorship. These Baronies all want to collect goods. They have properties and holdings that pledge allegiance to them and produce goods for them - but they also make extra!

If you're enterprising enough, you can go out there and buy those extra goods and bring them back to the Barony for profit. You'll also be helping the Baronies in question, though you don't have to take it to a specific Barony. You can sell those goods to any of the five baronies.

Supplies! Yes, right. Supplies are goods from the Barony that are meant only for the properties that Barony owns. You cannot purchase supplies and deliver them to another settlement, hamlet or guildhouse - they brand the boxes, you see.

Additionally, you can only deliver supplies to a location that actually needs them. But, when you do - that will speed the production of whatever goods they may have to sell to you to bring back to the Barony. Thus, the trade cycle continues and the Queen collects your Aenar.

Is there anything else I can do for you?
I see. And that business is?
